<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" FontFamily="Calibri">
    <Paragraph FontSize="24">Overview</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Interval component is designed to view on fretboard (or play) notes intervals.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontSize="24">Structure</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Interval component is represented by a table. Each row represents different interval with information os its:</Paragraph>
    <List>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Identifier</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Name</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Distance in semitones</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>
    <Paragraph>Last two columns of each row contains button "Show" and "Play". First button presents note on fretboard, second play root and interval note.
   Above table, button "Show selected" will print on fretboard all selected intervals in interval table.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontSize="24">Behavior</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Interval component require at least one note selected on fretboard (root note). If more then one note is selected then interval will be shown
   for lowest note. When excercise mode is enabled then interval component will look a bit different. It will contains buttons instead of table. Each button
   will contains a label with name of interval. This panel is used to enable user to provide an anwser e.g. which interval is shown or heard.</Paragraph>

</FlowDocument>